  "prompt": "How can I use markdown with django?",
  "response": "Using Markdown with Django involves converting Markdown content to HTML so it can be rendered in templates. Here's a step-by-step guide to achieve this:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Install a Markdown Library\nFirst, install a Markdown processing library like `markdown` or `markdown2`. You can install it using pip:\n\n```bash\npip install markdown\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Convert Markdown to HTML in Views\nIn your Django views, you can convert Markdown content to HTML using the library. For example:\n\n```python\nimport markdown\nfrom django.shortcuts import render\n\ndef my_view(request):\n    markdown_text = \"\"\"\n## Hello, Markdown!\nThis is a **bold** text and this is *italic*.\n    \"\"\"\n    html_content = markdown.markdown(markdown_text)  # Convert Markdown to HTML\n    return render(request, 'my_template.html', {'html_content': html_content})\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Render HTML in Templates\nIn your Django template, you can render the converted HTML content using the `|safe` filter to avoid escaping HTML tags:\n\n```html\n<!-- my_template.html -->\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <title>Markdown Example</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div>\n        {{ html_content|safe }}\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Optional: Use Django-Markdownx or Django-Markdownify for Advanced Features\nIf you need more advanced features like live Markdown editing or automatic template filters, consider using third-party Django packages like:\n\n- **Django-Markdownx**: Adds a Markdown editor widget for Django forms.\n  ```bash\n  pip install django-markdownx\n  ```\n\n- **Django-Markdownify**: Adds template filters and tags for Markdown processing.\n  ```bash\n  pip install django-markdownify\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Optional: Store Markdown in Models\nIf you want to store Markdown content in your database, you can use a `TextField` in your Django model:\n\n```python\nfrom django.db import models\n\nclass MyModel(models.Model):\n    markdown_content = models.TextField()\n\n    def html_content(self):\n        import markdown\n        return markdown.markdown(self.markdown_content)\n```\n\nThen render it in your template like this:\n```html\n<div>\n    {{ object.html_content|safe }}\n</div>\n```\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily integrate Markdown with Django and render it in your templates.",
